65.3	Coalition_Provisional_Authority	Coalition Provisional Authority	The Coalition Provisional Authority (Arabic: سلطة الائتلاف المؤقتة) was established as a transitional government following the invasion of Iraq by the United States and its allies, members of the Multi-National Force – Iraq which was formed to oust the government of Saddam Hussein in 2003. Citing United Nations Security Council Resolution 1483 (2003), and the laws of war, the CPA vested itself with executive, legislative, and judicial authority over the Iraqi government from the period of the CPA's inception on April 21, 2003, until its dissolution on June 28, 2004.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Flag_of_Iraq%2C_1991-2004.svg/125px-Flag_of_Iraq%2C_1991-2004.svg.png
